  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, bring the water to a boil.",
    "Add the currants, star anise, bay leaf, and sliced ginger to the boiling water.",
    "Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes until the currants soften.",
    "Stir in apple cider vinegar, sugar, salt, and pepper, and simmer for another 5 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from heat and strain the broth through a fine mesh sieve.",
    "Return the strained broth to the pot, add lemon zest, and heat just until warm.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve hot over rice or enjoy on its own."
